.TH THESAURUS "1" "December 2025" "202602020740-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
thesaurus \- Look up synonyms, antonyms, and related words
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B thesaurus
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR] [\fI\,WORD\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B thesaurus
is a script for looking up synonyms, antonyms, and related words. It provides comprehensive word lookup with support for rhyming words and topic-based searches.
.PP
The script uses online thesaurus APIs to find related words.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-help
Display help message with usage information and available options
.TP
.BR \-\-config
Generate or regenerate user configuration file with default settings
.TP
.BR \-\-version
Show script version information and exit
.TP
.BR \-\-options
Display all available command-line options
.TP
.BR \-\-debug
Enable debug mode with verbose output and command tracing (set -x)
.TP
.BR \-\-raw
Disable colorized output for plain text display
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B thesaurus happy
Find synonyms for "happy"
.TP
.B thesaurus --antonyms sad
Find antonyms for "sad"
.TP
.B thesaurus --rhyme cat
Find words that rhyme with "cat"
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.config/myscripts/thesaurus/settings.conf
User configuration file for thesaurus preferences
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error or no results found
.TP
.B 4
Network connection failed
